# Nimble Agent Builder — Always-Apply Rules

## The CLI is the only transport

All Nimble operations use CLI commands via Bash. There is no fallback transport —
if the CLI is missing, stop and follow `rules/setup.md`.

**Foreground — direct CLI calls:**

| Command | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `nimble agent list --limit 100` | Search for existing agents |
| `nimble agent get --template-name` | Display schema before run |
| `nimble agent run --agent --params` | Interactive execution |
| `nimble search` | Web search / discovery |

**Task agents — long-running operations (generate → poll → publish):**

| Command | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `nimble agent generate --agent-name --prompt --url` | Create or refine an agent |
| `nimble agent generate --from-agent --prompt` | Iterate on existing agent |
| `nimble agent get-generation --generation-id` | Poll generation status |
| `nimble agent publish --agent-name --version-id` | Publish a version |

Agent creation runs in a Task agent because generation takes 1-3 minutes.

## Update over generate — always

When `nimble agent list --limit 100` finds an agent on the same domain — even with missing fields or different scope — **update it** via `nimble agent generate --from-agent`. Do NOT generate a new agent from scratch.

Only generate from scratch when the agent list returns **zero matches** for the target domain.

## Every Task agent prompt must include the CLI commands

Copy this block into every Task agent prompt:

```
**CLI tools (use via Bash):**
- `nimble agent list --limit 100`
- `nimble agent get --template-name <name>`
- `nimble agent run --agent <name> --params '{...}'`
- `nimble agent generate --agent-name <name> --prompt "<prompt>" --url "<url>"`
- `nimble agent generate --agent-name <name> --from-agent <name> --prompt "<prompt>"`
- `nimble agent get-generation --generation-id <id>`
- `nimble agent publish --agent-name <name> --version-id <id>`
- `nimble search --query "<query>"`

Use the nimble CLI for all operations. Never curl Nimble API endpoints directly.
```

## Never use WebSearch or WebFetch

All web search must go through `nimble search` (CLI, via Bash). Never use `WebSearch`, `WebFetch`, `curl`, or `wget` — in the foreground or inside Task agents.

## Never use WSA tools

Never call `nimble_find_search_agent`, `nimble_run_search_agent`, or `nimble_url_extract`.
